snippet.textDisplay: I understand that you’re hiding behind the paper screen-defense that is “it’s a joke” but here’s the thing, good comedy music has to be mostly good. This is why I don’t enjoy comedy groups like Calpurnia and Starbomb, the lyrics, even if they are funny, are put in front of bland and tasteless composition to the point where it’s not funny, it’s just bad. This is what you did here, and I know you probably understand how to do this right, because you shot a music video that uses many tropes from mainstream high production pop music video production, yet the music is the most boring shit imaginable. Jokes that don’t have thought put into them aren’t generally funny, even if that seems counterintuitive.
